name: Vicio
description:
(= vice) : spanish noun

1.  (= inmoralidad) a particular form of depravity; depraved or degrading behavior
2.  (= mala costumbre) bad habit; weakness
3.  (= adicción) the drug habit; drug addiction
4.  (= corrupcion) moral depravity or corruption; wickedness : BUFFOON, JESTER
5.  (= defecto) a physical imperfection; taint : BLEMISH, DEFECT
(Law) error
(Linguistics) mistake; incorrect form
6. (con niño) excessive indulgence
7. (Latin America) to be idle
8.  (= vice) a bad or neurotic habit of stabled horses detrimental to their usefulness, typically arising as a result of boredom
